# 2012-09-07.rtb.1: Relicensing Debian Logos

### WHEREAS

1) The Debian Project Leader, Stefano Zacchiroli, has requested that SPI 
   relicense the Debian logos listed in paragraph 5 below to meet the 
   Debian Free Software Guidelines.

2) The Debian Project Leader, has sought and obtained legal advice on
   relicense the Debian logos and has presented this advice to the Board.

3) The Debian Project lists and depicts each of its licenses at [http://www.debian.org/logos/](http://www.debian.org/logos/).

### THE BOARD RESOLVES that:

4) Resolution [2008-03-19.jrk.2](/corporate/resolutions/2008/2008-03-19.jrk.2/) is repealed.

5) The Debian logos being relicensed are:

<pre>
   a) The Debian Open Use Logo depicting a red swirl with the word "Debian"
   b) The Debian Open Use Logo depicting a red swirl without the word "Debian"
</pre>

6) The Debian logos listed in paragraph 5 above are relicensed under the 
   [GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL) version 3](http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl.html) or later,
   or, at the recipient's option, [Creative Commons Attribution Share-alike license (CC-BY-SA) 3.0](http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/legalcode).

7) Any use of the term "this software" within one of the licenses mentioned in paragraph 6 above shall refer to the logo itself.

